Step 1: Identify the Operating Cash Flow from the cash flow statement.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –13,358,400.82

Step 2: Identify the Total Current Liabilities from the balance sheet (at the end date).  
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,903,121.89

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the formula:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)

Step 4: Perform the calculation:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = –13,358,400.82 / 1,903,121.89 ≈ –7.02

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is approximately –7.02.
